refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arraygetopt stringoptions arraylongopts
Returns an associative array of option / argument pairs based on the options format specified in options, or &false; on an error.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 This function will return an array of option / argument pairs.  If an
 option does not have an argument, the value will be set to &false;.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     5.3.0

      This function is no longer system dependent and works on Windows too.

  &reftitle.examples;



    getopt Example


<?php
// parse the command line ($GLOBALS['argv'])
$options = getopt("f:hp:");
?>
